    "steps": [
        "Put a large saucepan on a medium heat and add 1 tbsp olive oil.",
        "Add 4 finely chopped bacon rashers and fry for 10 mins until golden and crisp.",
        "Reduce the heat and add the onions, carrots, celery sticks, garlic cloves and the leaves from 2-3 sprigs rosemary, all finely chopped, then fry for 10 mins. Stir the veg often until it softens.",
        "Increase the heat to medium-high, add beef mince and cook stirring for 3-4 mins until the meat is browned all over.",
        "Add the ingredients for the Bolognese sauce. Stir with a wooden spoon, breaking up the plum tomatoes.",
        "Bring to the boil, reduce to a gentle simmer and cover with a lid. Cook for 1 hr 15 mins stirring occasionally, until you have a rich, thick sauce.",
        "Serve bolognese with spaghetti and grated parmesan. Garnish with basil leaves."
